This paper focuses on measuring the impact of scholarly books using a range of indicators, including altmetrics, views, downloads, and citations. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and machine learning (cs.LG), as these fields often involve the analysis and evaluation of scholarly publications.
